Native American Shipwrecks
Franklin Watts | 2000 | 0531203794 | English | 72 pages | PDF | 9 MB

Shipwrecks tell many stories of society, history, people, and technology. Through the study of underwater vessels and particular shipwrecks, students will learn about the evolution of sea-faring vessels, the missions of war that ended at the bottom of the sea, and the important role shipwrecks have had on our history
